# Project Context — Redis Learning App

## Stack
- Java 21 (GraalVM 21 — SDKMAN or Winget installed)
- Gradle 9.x with Kotlin DSL (build.gradle.kts)
- Spring Boot 4.0.x
- Spring Data Redis (Lettuce client)
- Spring Cache abstraction (@EnableCaching)
- PostgreSQL 16 via Docker
- Redis 7 via Docker
- Lombok for boilerplate reduction

## Key Constraints
- Windows 11 with WSL2 for Docker
- GraalVM native compilation is NOT used in dev; only JVM mode
- No Maven — always use Gradle tasks (./gradlew, not mvn)
- Jackson is the serializer for Redis values (JSON, not Java serialization)
- All entity classes must be Serializable AND have no-arg constructors for Jackson

## Conventions
- Package structure: com.redis.postgres.{model,service,repository,controller,config}
- Redis key format: {cacheName}:{entityId} e.g. products:prod-123
- All cache names declared in CacheConfig enum, not hardcoded strings
- application.yml (not .properties), separate application-test.yml for test profile
- Docker compose file at project root: docker-compose.yml

## Testing
- JUnit 5 + Mockito for unit tests
- @SpringBootTest + Testcontainers for integration tests
- Test profile uses embedded Redis (via Testcontainers, NOT spring-boot-starter-data-redis-test)

## Do NOT
- Do not use Java serialization for Redis values (use Jackson JSON)
- Do not use @Autowired (use constructor injection)
- Do not hardcode localhost — use environment variables with docker-compose